     >  Overview

        This repository installs configuration files for software
        that I use on a regular basis:

          - vim & neovim
          - tmux
          - Zsh
          - git
          - etc.

        These are my dotfiles, meaning they're mainly used on hardware
        that I own and run—typically debian and macos. In general, things
        should Just Work™, so open an issue if you run into problems.

     >  Installation

        $ git clone --recursive https://github.com/geiger-to/dotfiles.git
        $ cd dotfiles && ./install.rb

        ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ WARNING: Review the Brewfile and backup your existing configs   │
        │ before running. install.rb will overwrite your existing `vimrc`,│
        │ `tmux.conf`, `zshrc`, and other config files. It will also run  │
        │ `brew bundle` and install a bunch of software. Additionally,    │
        │ it will prompt for your name and email to configure git.        │
        └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

     >  Getting Started

        After installation, for proper color support in iTerm2:

        1. Import the Catppuccin Mocha theme:
           iTerm2 > Settings > Profiles > Colors > Color Presets > Import...
           Select `iterm/catppuccin-mocha.itermcolors`

        2. Import the profile:
           iTerm2 > Settings > Profiles > Other Actions > Import JSON Profiles...
           Select `iterm/profile.json`

        3. Enable the imported profile:
           Settings > Profiles > select the imported profile and set as default

        4. Restart iTerm2

     >  Usage

        I open projects with the following in iTerm2 + zsh:

            > proj ...

        `proj` will create or connect to a TMUX session of the same name.
        It will also set the working directory to `~/Projects/${name}`.

     >  TMUX

        I use tmux for "project" management.

        ┌─ Session Management ──────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Ctrl-Space> d              detach from session               │
        │ <Ctrl-Space> r              reload tmux configuration         │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ Window Management ───────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Ctrl-Space> c              create new window                 │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ Pane Management ─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Ctrl-Space> v              split window horizontally         │
        │ <Ctrl-Space> s              split window vertically           │
        │ <Ctrl-Space> x              close current pane                │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ Pane Navigation ─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Ctrl-Space> h              move to pane left                 │
        │ <Ctrl-Space> j              move to pane down                 │
        │ <Ctrl-Space> k              move to pane up                   │
        │ <Ctrl-Space> l              move to pane right                │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

     >  Vim

        I use it for editing and debugging code in my projects.

        ┌─ Basic Navigation ────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ jj/ESC                      escape to normal mode             │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ File Operations ─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Space> w                   write file                        │
        │ <Space> wq                  write and quit                    │
        │ <Space> q                   quit                              │
        │ <Space> rm                  delete current file               │
        │ <Space> fo                  open file in Finder               │
        │ <Space> fn                  copy filename to clipboard        │
        │ <Space> fp                  copy filepath to clipboard        │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ File Explorer ───────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Space> e                   toggle file explorer              │
        │ <Space> -                   show file explorer                │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ Search & Replace ────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Space> p                   fuzzy file search                 │
        │ <Space> a                   search with ag                    │
        │ <Space> fs                  Far search                        │
        │ <Space> fr                  Far replace                       │
        │ <Space> <Space>             toggle search highlighting        │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ Window & Split Management ───────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Space> v                   create vertical split             │
        │ <Space> s                   create horizontal split           │
        │ <Space> m                   maximize split                    │
        │ <Ctrl-h>                    move to left split                │
        │ <Ctrl-j>                    move to down split                │
        │ <Ctrl-k>                    move to up split                  │
        │ <Ctrl-l>                    move to right split               │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ Code Editing ────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Ctrl-l> (visual)           indent right                      │
        │ <Ctrl-h> (visual)           indent left                       │
        │ \\                          toggle comment                    │
        │ <Space> (visual)            easy align                        │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ Development Tools ───────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Space> o                   toggle tagbar outline             │
        │ <Space> db                  open database UI                  │
        │ <Space> S                   open Spectre                      │
        │ <Space> k                   show documentation                │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

        ┌─ Git Integration ─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ <Space> gg                  git status/commit interface       │
        │ <Space> gd                  toggle git diff gutter            │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

     >  Git

        I use `git feature` (from [git-extras](https://github.com/tj/git-extras)) 
        for most PR branches, except when editing directly in GitHub.

        Thanks!
